  "texts": [
    "For example, quantifying the effects of mutations on multiple molecular phenotypes and in multiple genetic backgrounds-an approach called \"multidimensional mutagenesis\"-has allowed us to infer changes in the folding and binding energies for tens of thousands of mutations in human protein domains [15,16].",
    "Neural networks provide a fast and convenient approach to quantitatively study genotype-phenotype (G-P) maps and are increasingly being used to model DMS data [7,[15][16][17][18][19][20].",
    "Although general-use software tools for this purpose have been developed [7,[19][20][21][22][23][24][25], none as yet permit mechanistic models to be fit to this type of multi-phenotype and complex genotype DMS data in a flexible manner (Table 1).",
    "To address this need, we have developed MoCHI, a software tool that allows the parameterization of arbitrarily complex models using DMS data.",
    "MoCHI simplifies the task of building custom models from measurements of mutant effects on any number of phenotypes.A further challenge is represented by the fact that the phenotypic outcome of a mutation often depends on the genetic context (or background) in which it occurs."
  ],
